---
import UntranslatedLayout from '~/layouts/UntranslatedLayout.astro';
---

<UntranslatedLayout
    title="Terms of Service | Inurri"
    description="Terms for contacting Inurri and starting website or web application work."
>
    <div class="pt-32 pb-24">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
            <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-8">Terms of Service</h1>
            <div class="prose dark:prose-invert max-w-none text-foreground/80">
                <p class="text-lg mb-6">Last updated: July 19, 2026</p>

                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-4 text-foreground">1. Scope</h2>
                <p>
                    This page gives a simple overview of the terms that apply when you use the Inurri website or contact me about a possible website, web application, automation, or related service.
                </p>

                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-4 text-foreground">2. Website information</h2>
                <p>
                    The content on this website is provided for general information. Project scope, pricing, timelines, and responsibilities are confirmed individually before work starts.
                </p>

                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-4 text-foreground">3. Project work</h2>
                <p>
                    Sending a message through the website does not create a contract or obligation to start work. Any paid project begins only after the scope, price, schedule, payment terms, and other practical details are agreed separately.
                </p>

                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-4 text-foreground">4. Client materials</h2>
                <p>
                    If you provide text, images, logos, access credentials, or other materials for a project, you are responsible for making sure you have the right to use them and share them for the agreed work.
                </p>

                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-4 text-foreground">5. Intellectual property</h2>
                <p>
                    Ownership and usage rights for project deliverables are agreed per project. Reusable code, components, tools, and know-how that are not created exclusively for one client may remain reusable by Inurri unless agreed otherwise.
                </p>

                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-4 text-foreground">6. Limitation of liability</h2>
                <p>
                    The website is provided as-is. I try to keep information accurate and the website available, but I cannot guarantee that it will always be error-free or uninterrupted.
                </p>

                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-4 text-foreground">7. Changes</h2>
                <p>
                    These terms may be updated when the website, services, or business process changes. The updated date above shows when this page was last revised.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</UntranslatedLayout>
